=================
How does it work?
=================

    Now I'll try to explain why ESP works better than other archivers. ESP's
 algorithm is almost the same as the one other archivers use. The main
 differences are two.
    The first is:  ESP compresses in a SOLID format (that means that before
 compressing the files it merges all files into one, and then compresses
 them. When decompressing, ESP decompresses first and then cuts
 the package to files), but it sorts the files by type, what means that
 text, graphic and other files will be near the same type.
    The second one is: ESP detects the same beginnings of files, for
 example in text-files, when all of them have got the same header, etc.
 You can switch this function off by using the /J switch.

